1
00:00:39,040 --> 00:00:41,751
Yeah, Lester.

2
00:00:41,834 --> 00:00:43,753
- Where are you at?
- On monk in east Baltimore.

3
00:00:43,836 --> 00:00:45,546
- Who's on marlo?
- No one right now.

4
00:00:45,630 --> 00:00:47,048
Marlo's been the hardest to follow.

5
00:00:47,131 --> 00:00:49,634
Too paranoid.
Too much counter-surveillance.

6
00:00:49,717 --> 00:00:55,556
Well, peel off monk and head out
broening highway to the marine terminals.

7
00:00:55,640 --> 00:01:00,436
Map 44, grid g-as-in-George 10.

8
00:01:01,187 --> 00:01:03,606
- 44.
- Affirmative. This is a fresh one.

9
00:01:03,689 --> 00:01:06,234
If they're going all the way out there,
it mightjust be...

10
00:01:06,317 --> 00:01:08,486
- Damn right.
- On it.

11
00:01:09,487 --> 00:01:13,282
23-06 to all units on this detail.
New 20 is map 44.

12
00:01:13,366 --> 00:01:14,700
Grid g-George 10.

13
00:01:14,784 --> 00:01:16,535
That's 44 g-George 10.

14
00:01:16,619 --> 00:01:18,663
Flood that grid and
look for suspect vehicles.

15
00:01:18,746 --> 00:01:21,165
23-12.10-4.

16
00:01:21,249 --> 00:01:24,252
Take me a while. I'm up northeast.
You want me to stay on cheese?

17
00:01:24,335 --> 00:01:27,338
Negative. New 20 is a priority.
Think we're on the main stem.

18
00:01:58,703 --> 00:02:01,455
- Yeah?
- Mcnulty. It's on.

19
00:02:01,539 --> 00:02:03,708
- Yeah?
- Oh, hell, yeah.

20
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:05,459
All right.

21
00:02:27,565 --> 00:02:30,860
When you walk through the garden

22
00:02:32,028 --> 00:02:33,904
gotta watch your back

23
00:02:36,324 --> 00:02:38,576
well, I beg your pardon

24
00:02:40,077 --> 00:02:42,747
walk the straight and narrow track

25
00:02:44,832 --> 00:02:46,417
if you walk with Jesus

26
00:02:49,211 --> 00:02:51,630
he's gonna save your soul

27
00:02:54,300 --> 00:03:00,264
you gotta keep the devil way down in a hole

28
00:03:11,067 --> 00:03:13,235
He's got the fire and the fury

29
00:03:16,113 --> 00:03:17,740
at his command

30
00:03:20,117 --> 00:03:22,203
well, you don't have to worry

31
00:03:24,205 --> 00:03:27,124
if you hold on to Jesus' hand

32
00:03:28,626 --> 00:03:30,628
and we'll all be safe from Satan

33
00:03:33,089 --> 00:03:35,216
when the thunder rolls

34
00:03:37,635 --> 00:03:40,304
but you gotta help me keep the devil

35
00:03:41,931 --> 00:03:43,641
way down in the hole

36
00:03:44,433 --> 00:03:46,560
in the bottom of the hole

37
00:03:48,354 --> 00:03:50,147
in the hole in the hole

38
00:03:50,773 --> 00:03:52,608
way down in the hole

39
00:03:53,067 --> 00:03:55,236
in the hole in the hole

40
00:03:57,363 --> 00:03:59,198
in the hole in the hole

41
00:03:59,365 --> 00:04:00,908
way down in the hole

42
00:04:24,265 --> 00:04:25,766
Ok, whatcha got?

43
00:04:25,850 --> 00:04:28,269
We rolled around until
Bobby spotted Chris partlow

44
00:04:28,352 --> 00:04:30,271
pulled up on a lot two blocks from here.

45
00:04:30,354 --> 00:04:34,275
So we sat on him until marlo posted. They
talked for a minute, then marlo bounced.

46
00:04:34,358 --> 00:04:37,695
And Chris goes to the warehouse gate alone
and a coupla white boys open up.

47
00:04:37,778 --> 00:04:38,988
He's inside now?

48
00:04:39,071 --> 00:04:42,783
Entrance is around front, it's the only
working gate. Everything else is rusted up.

49
00:04:42,867 --> 00:04:44,427
- Who's watching the front?
- Two units.

50
00:04:44,452 --> 00:04:47,872
They're on foot, a block away,
with a clear view of what comes in or out.

51
00:04:47,955 --> 00:04:49,623
So what do we do if Chris rolls out?

52
00:04:49,707 --> 00:04:52,960
Let him go. Partlow is muscle.
He's here to make sure it looks right.

53
00:04:53,043 --> 00:04:55,796
And if it does,
monk or someone else'il come on down.

54
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:57,840
- Cheese, too, maybe.
- So this is a re-up.

55
00:04:57,923 --> 00:05:02,011
Fuck a re-up, son.
This, here, in the middle of nowhere...

56
00:05:02,094 --> 00:05:06,599
Miles from anywhere these mopes meet...
This is re-supply.

57
00:05:06,682 --> 00:05:08,726
Other than Chris,
anybody else that goes in there,

58
00:05:08,809 --> 00:05:12,104
if it's a Stanfield lieutenant,
he's coming out dirty.

59
00:05:12,313 --> 00:05:15,733
Follow them back to town. If he doesn't
know you're on 'em, see where he takes you.

60
00:05:15,816 --> 00:05:17,651
If he catches a scent, fuck it.

61
00:05:17,735 --> 00:05:20,321
Pull 'em over, Jack 'em
up and get the dope.

62
00:05:20,404 --> 00:05:25,618
And leander, you want to snatch the man's
cell before he has a chance to erase anything.

63
00:05:25,701 --> 00:05:28,037
The case is in the phones...

64
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:30,664
Though we're gonna need a title three
to take a look at them.

65
00:05:30,748 --> 00:05:31,916
Where are you going?

66
00:05:34,001 --> 00:05:35,211
Time to 'fess up.

67
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:39,465
We straight?

68
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:42,593
I said we straight, right?

69
00:05:43,761 --> 00:05:46,347
- Them guns was mine.
- Which guns specifically, Mr. Hill?

70
00:05:46,430 --> 00:05:50,142
Whatever guns them cops
took out the truck last year. They mine.

71
00:05:50,351 --> 00:05:52,478
Even though I ain't touched that iron.

72
00:05:53,562 --> 00:05:55,189
Ain't you got to do the bit.

73
00:05:55,272 --> 00:05:59,360
With your limited priors, Mr. Hill,
you're exposed to two, three years, tops.

74
00:05:59,443 --> 00:06:01,403
You'll be well compensated
for the time, I'm sure.

75
00:06:01,445 --> 00:06:04,365
No good to us no how. You on three legs.

76
00:06:04,448 --> 00:06:07,928
Familiarize yourself with the make and model
of the weapons you left in the truck, Mr. Hill.

77
00:06:07,952 --> 00:06:11,205
- The details matter.
- I get shot up an' then this shit.

78
00:06:11,288 --> 00:06:14,750
- Y'all ask a lot, don'tcha?
- You can't hack, go down Wal-Mart.

79
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:17,336
And see if they take care you
while you laid up for a while.

80
00:06:17,419 --> 00:06:18,879
C'mon, nigger.

81
00:06:27,137 --> 00:06:29,515
Jeez. In the department,
you take one in the line

82
00:06:29,598 --> 00:06:31,809
they give you light duty
for as long as you need,

83
00:06:31,892 --> 00:06:35,646
- then you get to name your next assignment.
- Marlo runs a tighter ship.

84
00:06:54,665 --> 00:06:56,834
Open it.

85
00:07:11,181 --> 00:07:13,767
Six icebox, 20 each.

86
00:07:13,851 --> 00:07:15,436
You count, we wait.

87
00:07:15,519 --> 00:07:18,814
You no count, we go to lunch early.

88
00:07:57,936 --> 00:08:00,189
23-14 to 23-06.

89
00:08:00,272 --> 00:08:02,483
Suspect number three is in.

90
00:08:02,566 --> 00:08:05,444
- You sure?
- Been following the damn truck for a week.

91
00:08:05,527 --> 00:08:07,404
- Should know by now.
- Copy that.

92
00:08:07,488 --> 00:08:09,490
Ticks have six legs or eight?

93
00:08:15,371 --> 00:08:17,164
Must have been a readjustment.

94
00:08:17,247 --> 00:08:20,751
London was a sweet posting. I can't lie.

95
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:24,171
My only regret is
I didn't get the full three-year tour.

96
00:08:24,254 --> 00:08:27,049
- Thanks.
- It's no reflection on you, man.

97
00:08:27,132 --> 00:08:29,968
Shit, Gus, they even sold
the building in Kensington.

98
00:08:30,052 --> 00:08:32,638
We bought that sucker
for nothing 50 years ago,

99
00:08:32,721 --> 00:08:36,308
and now Chicago sells it off
for a couple million pounds.

100
00:08:36,392 --> 00:08:38,352
Capitalization, they call it.

101
00:08:38,435 --> 00:08:42,147
These newspaper chain guys
just don't give a fuck, do they?

102
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:46,193
Any idea where they're gonna drop you now
that you're back in charm city?

103
00:08:46,276 --> 00:08:48,404
No, I got no idea yet.

104
00:08:48,487 --> 00:08:52,324
Klebanow wants to have lunch,
so I guess it'll come at me soon enough.

105
00:08:52,408 --> 00:08:55,035
Up for something now?

106
00:08:55,119 --> 00:08:56,412
Depends.

107
00:08:57,746 --> 00:09:00,040
I gotta problem. I need someone...

108
00:09:00,124 --> 00:09:04,086
A veteran reporter, quiet,
subtle, discreet, good with details,

109
00:09:04,169 --> 00:09:06,088
careful to cover his tracks...

110
00:09:06,171 --> 00:09:09,466
I don't care how far we go back, Gus,
no way I'm gonna kill your wife for you.

111
00:09:11,635 --> 00:09:14,012
You know Scott Templeton? City ga.

112
00:09:14,096 --> 00:09:16,265
The guy talking to the homeless killer?

113
00:09:16,348 --> 00:09:17,349
Not really.

114
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:21,061
- He got hired after I went to London.
- It's better you don't know him.

115
00:09:21,145 --> 00:09:22,980
No opinions one way or the other.

116
00:09:23,981 --> 00:09:25,566
No, no, I'm not saying anything.

117
00:09:25,774 --> 00:09:29,445
I'm not. I just need fresh eyes
on the fella. Just a careful look.

118
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:34,324
- One of whiting's pets, isn't he?
- I said discreet.

119
00:09:35,951 --> 00:09:39,663
- I hope you're wrong.
- Course you do.

120
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:46,420
- It sticks. Dag.
- Course it sticks. It's Barb wire.

121
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:48,505
Sticking's what it's s'posed to do.

122
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:51,967
Come on. I ain't got all day.

123
00:09:56,305 --> 00:09:59,183
Hurry up now.
Grab the aluminum strips there first off.

124
00:10:17,117 --> 00:10:20,287
- How am I supposed to get back over?
- Climb the damn fence.

125
00:10:20,370 --> 00:10:23,123
Do a betterjob of it second time, I expect.

126
00:10:23,207 --> 00:10:25,876
Grab them steel pipes quick
before we get spotted.

127
00:10:39,848 --> 00:10:41,558
- Robert.
- Hey.

128
00:10:41,642 --> 00:10:43,101
- Welcome home.
- Thanks.

129
00:10:43,185 --> 00:10:47,981
I need a global printout on everything
under Scott Templeton's byline.

130
00:10:48,065 --> 00:10:49,358
All of it, every edition.

131
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,819
Hey, I'm a fan.

132
00:11:13,382 --> 00:11:14,925
23-14.

133
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:19,263
Monk is westbound onto O'Donnell.
Cheese wagstaff is on the way in.

134
00:11:19,346 --> 00:11:23,016
Also, there's a truck leaving,
the one we saw back on the loading dock.

135
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:26,103
That'd be empty. They've
offloaded, it's all in the warehouse now.

136
00:11:26,186 --> 00:11:31,108
Bobby and me will stay on monk. Karen'll
follow cheese out, you guys stay on the gate.

137
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:39,366
Forgetting for a moment
our little problem of the serial killer,

138
00:11:39,449 --> 00:11:42,411
we came in promising a double-digit drop
in violent crime.

139
00:11:42,494 --> 00:11:46,248
Right up on the gubernatorial primary,
and we're looking at another record high.

140
00:11:46,331 --> 00:11:49,334
Michael, this department has been crippled
by the budget cuts.

141
00:11:49,418 --> 00:11:52,921
For a year now, we haven't had
the manpower or the tools.

142
00:11:53,130 --> 00:11:55,210
- You have them now.
- Now. But this thing is a ship.

143
00:11:55,257 --> 00:11:59,011
A super-tanker.
We can't just turn it around like that.

144
00:11:59,094 --> 00:12:01,054
More foot patrols.
More cars on the street.

145
00:12:01,138 --> 00:12:02,723
Get a handle on it, dammit.

146
00:12:02,931 --> 00:12:05,225
See, that's what doesn't work.

147
00:12:05,309 --> 00:12:08,395
More cops where people can see them.
More cops on the pavement,

148
00:12:08,478 --> 00:12:11,315
more cops riding past,
more cops showing the flag

149
00:12:11,398 --> 00:12:13,567
so that you guys can say
you're being tough on crime.

150
00:12:13,650 --> 00:12:18,447
Respectfully, sir, what works
is committing to building a real deterrent.

151
00:12:18,530 --> 00:12:22,075
We take the time to retool,
to teach our people not to chase stats,

152
00:12:22,159 --> 00:12:25,412
- but to do actual police work.
- Who pulled your string, deputy?

153
00:12:25,495 --> 00:12:30,250
I was told by our mayor at the outset
that there would be no more band-aids,

154
00:12:30,334 --> 00:12:31,585
no more stat games...

155
00:12:31,668 --> 00:12:35,297
Then we got hit with the school budget. And
lost some of the time we needed to address

156
00:12:35,380 --> 00:12:37,341
the systemic things you're talking about.

157
00:12:37,424 --> 00:12:39,509
Understood. We will work back on those,

158
00:12:39,593 --> 00:12:42,679
and we will support that kind of reform,
if not from city hall

159
00:12:42,763 --> 00:12:44,598
then from Annapolis, if need be.

160
00:12:44,681 --> 00:12:48,769
But now, deputy, right now,
my boss needs the crime to go down.

161
00:12:48,977 --> 00:12:51,688
Not three years from now.
Not even a year from now.

162
00:12:51,772 --> 00:12:55,609
He needs a ten per cent drop
in the next quarter...

163
00:12:55,692 --> 00:13:00,238
Or no one is gonna be in a position
to reform anything.

164
00:13:08,205 --> 00:13:10,165
Be creative, gentlemen.

165
00:13:19,549 --> 00:13:21,969
Deputy. A detective's outside for you,

166
00:13:22,052 --> 00:13:23,387
says it's urgent.

167
00:13:29,643 --> 00:13:31,228
Sydnor and I developed a source

168
00:13:31,311 --> 00:13:34,272
and ran fresh surveillances
on marlo Stanfield.

169
00:13:34,356 --> 00:13:37,150
And we believe
we're about to catch his people very dirty.

170
00:13:37,234 --> 00:13:39,194
- What?
- We wrapped on that Clay Davis thing

171
00:13:39,277 --> 00:13:41,029
and instead of shutting major crimes down,

172
00:13:41,113 --> 00:13:43,365
we took a couple weeks
and got back on marlo.

173
00:13:43,448 --> 00:13:46,451
With the right warrants,
he's about to fall.

174
00:13:46,535 --> 00:13:48,495
- How the fuck...
- There's no time, Cedric.

175
00:13:48,578 --> 00:13:51,456
In an hour or so, I'm gonna need...

176
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:54,835
Yeah?

177
00:13:55,043 --> 00:13:56,503
- Lester...
- What's up?

178
00:13:56,586 --> 00:13:58,380
We pulled up monk.
Dirty as a motherfucker.

179
00:13:58,463 --> 00:14:00,465
- Mm.
- Eight keys of the raw.

180
00:14:00,549 --> 00:14:03,027
No, he Jersey-rolled a stop and when
we tried to pull him over,

181
00:14:03,051 --> 00:14:04,678
he went rabbit on us.

182
00:14:04,761 --> 00:14:06,722
We ran him down on Lafayette,
by the overpass.

183
00:14:06,805 --> 00:14:10,350
- You got the phone, right?
- Yeah, man. I got it.

184
00:14:10,434 --> 00:14:11,852
Good work.

185
00:14:12,436 --> 00:14:13,645
It's down.

186
00:14:13,729 --> 00:14:17,691
I need teams to arrest marlo Stanfield,
Chris partlow, and cheese wagstaff.

187
00:14:17,774 --> 00:14:20,485
I also need someone from our Sao
to get on the horn

188
00:14:20,569 --> 00:14:23,697
to Baltimore county for an s-and-s warrant
on a middle river warehouse.

189
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:25,240
And, oh, yeah...

190
00:14:26,241 --> 00:14:29,494
Bunk moreland has a warrant on partlow

191
00:14:29,578 --> 00:14:30,996
for a separate homicide.

192
00:14:31,079 --> 00:14:33,206
He held that back
so we could do this business here.

193
00:14:33,290 --> 00:14:35,685
Anything else you've neglected to tell me,
detective freamon?

194
00:14:35,709 --> 00:14:38,503
No, sir. I think you're caught up.

195
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,052
- Hello?
- Ronnie, dear.

196
00:14:45,135 --> 00:14:46,261
Hey...

197
00:14:46,344 --> 00:14:48,138
- Are you sitting down?
- Why?

198
00:15:00,317 --> 00:15:01,902
Down, down, down, down!

199
00:15:01,985 --> 00:15:03,987
Let me see your hands!

200
00:15:05,155 --> 00:15:06,990
Get down!

201
00:15:09,326 --> 00:15:10,368
Get on the floor!

202
00:15:22,339 --> 00:15:24,424
He was trying to erase shit
when we tackled him.

203
00:15:45,237 --> 00:15:48,949
Secure this location
until we have written search-and-seizure.

204
00:17:02,981 --> 00:17:04,065
Shit's on TV, yo.

205
00:17:07,611 --> 00:17:11,656
With a street value of
almost sixteen million dollars in heroin,

206
00:17:11,865 --> 00:17:14,117
and charges against high-level traffickers

207
00:17:14,201 --> 00:17:17,329
who were going to put this poison
on the streets of this city...

208
00:17:17,412 --> 00:17:20,582
Do this mean I still gotta take
that charge for y'all?

209
00:17:20,665 --> 00:17:24,669
Hard work, determination and
perseverance by our police department.

210
00:17:24,878 --> 00:17:27,547
And while I am told that
this investigation is continuing,

211
00:17:27,631 --> 00:17:31,259
it is my understanding
that there is at least one murder warrant

212
00:17:31,343 --> 00:17:35,388
associated with this drug organization,
which is believed to have been responsible

213
00:17:35,472 --> 00:17:38,975
for many of those bodies found
in vacant row houses more than a year ago.

214
00:17:39,059 --> 00:17:43,188
We did not give up on that investigation
just as we do not give up trying every day

215
00:17:43,271 --> 00:17:48,109
to address ourselves to the task
of making this city safe and vibrant again.

216
00:17:48,193 --> 00:17:50,403
Let me just say to all
others responsible for

217
00:17:50,487 --> 00:17:53,073
the drug trade's assault
on the welfare of this city,

218
00:17:53,156 --> 00:17:55,533
a day like this is coming for you.

219
00:17:55,617 --> 00:17:57,118
Oh, you are so butch.

220
00:17:57,202 --> 00:17:59,246
I have seen what drugs
have done to Baltimore.

221
00:17:59,329 --> 00:18:03,208
Drug dealers do not just destroy
individuals. They destroy families.

222
00:18:03,291 --> 00:18:07,337
- Don't forget the communities.
- They destroy entire communities.

223
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:10,548
Today the mayor of Baltimore,
our state's attorney,

224
00:18:10,632 --> 00:18:13,176
our police department,
and our communities are saying,

225
00:18:13,260 --> 00:18:16,096
"we have had enough." Thank you.

226
00:18:20,976 --> 00:18:23,937
Deputy. Alma Gutierrez, sun papers.

227
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:27,148
- Care to comment?
- It's a good day for the good guys.

228
00:18:27,232 --> 00:18:29,359
Could you be a bit more substantive?

229
00:18:31,152 --> 00:18:33,947
Last time the sun had me in its pages,

230
00:18:34,030 --> 00:18:36,449
- you had me doing things I didn't do.
- Regarding?

231
00:18:36,533 --> 00:18:39,119
Something about me
stabbing someone in the back.

232
00:18:39,202 --> 00:18:40,370
Look it up.

233
00:18:48,712 --> 00:18:51,214
"A source of information

234
00:18:51,298 --> 00:18:55,635
"identified the transmission of photographs
via cellphone."

235
00:18:55,719 --> 00:18:58,305
Fuck do that mean?
"Source of information."

236
00:18:58,388 --> 00:19:01,516
- They sayin' somebody talkin'?
